@klamonte touched a point I'd like to stress.

I never used double width on Linux terminals because it's not there. I mean, it's there, on xterm or Konsole, but using each one causes some pains I'd prefer to avoid. Worst - they aren't the default. Besides, Gnome Terminal is my favorite (on the Mac, the crown goes to iTerm2) and works great.

For the same reasons, I never used sixel graphics. Or ReGis. Tek 4010 I used, but mostly for fun. I can imagine a ton of creative ways to put all those capabilities to good use in software, but they'll never have any real users if the theoretical standards behind them never get implemented.
